<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3132: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Feely</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                    Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-21T18:00:00-04:00">May 21, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 22—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>49. Department’s telegram 15, May 20, 3 p.m. The same reply was sent to
                            Chile but instead of being handed to the Chilean Minister here it was
                            delivered to the Chilean Foreign Office by the Bolivian Minister at
                            Santiago.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Feely</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>